# Install Jenkins using the OFFICIAL WAR + systemd method
(This is production-grade and recommended for Ubuntu 24.04)

## STEP 1 – Install Java 17
`sudo apt update`                  
`sudo apt install openjdk-17-jdk -y`                  
### Verify:
`java -version`                

## STEP 2 – Download Jenkins WAR (Official)
`wget https://get.jenkins.io/war-stable/latest/jenkins.war`               

## STEP 3 – Create Jenkins Service
`sudo vi /etc/systemd/system/jenkins.service`              
### Paste:
[Unit]              
Description=Jenkins                 
After=network.target                   

[Service]                
User=ubuntu                 
ExecStart=/usr/bin/java -jar /home/ubuntu/jenkins.war                   
Restart=always                

[Install]               
WantedBy=multi-user.target                 

## STEP 4 – Start Jenkins
`sudo systemctl daemon-reload`                 
`sudo systemctl start jenkins`                     
`sudo systemctl enable jenkins`                   
### Check:
`sudo systemctl status jenkins`               

## STEP 5 – Open Jenkins
`http://YOUR_EC2_IP:8080`             
### Get password:
`cat ~/.jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword`                 
